of legal and extralegal repression of publication can also become the stuff of news about news makers. When the subjects of news inhabit multiple participant roles in the unfolding of public events, when the very technologies of recording and circulating events themselves become news, the act of representing a political event becomes difficult to disentangle from that of participating in it. This, Cody argues, is the crisis of contemporary news making: the news can no longer claim exteriority to the world on which it reports.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aDigital mediaxPolitical aspectszIndiazTamil Nadu. 0aDigital media-Political aspects-India-Tamil Nadu. 0aJournalismxPolitical aspectszIndiazTamil Nadu. 0aJournalism-Political aspects-India-Tamil Nadu. 0aMass mediaxPolitical aspectszIndiazTamil Nadu. 0aMass media-Political aspects-India-Tamil Nadu. 0aTamil Nadu (India)-Politics and government-21st century. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  amedia, India, journalism, democracy, Tamil, event, anthropology, popular sovereignty, law, news.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Cultural and Area Studies 2023 Englishz978311131909408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Cultural and Area Studies 2023z978311131812708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079732940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226824741423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226824741/original  a978-3-11-079732-9  University of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-1318